        <h2>Frequetly Asked Questions</h2>
       <strong> Our most commonly asked questions:</strong>
        <p>
            1.Our criteria for acceptance:<br />
            Our target group is 15 – 22 year olds who are at risk in their current living arrangements. A sense of desire and willingness to adhere to smiling youth guidelines is a key focus for acceptance into the youth Program.

        </p>
        <p>
            2. Where do the young people live? <br />
            Our organization accommodates young people in suburban homes within the Melbourne metropolitan area and regional Victoria. The smiling youth Foundation took possession of its first home early in 1994.
        </p>
        <strong> Volunteer asked questions:</strong>
        <p>
            1. Can i volunteer if i work full time?<br />
            Smiling Youth Foundation has a variety of volunteer opportunities, some within business hours and some outside. If you work full time there are many opportunities such as joining a community committee, assisting in maintenance at the home, participating in an event or general fundraising. These positions are all vital to the operation of the Foundation, if you believe you could help please register your details in our volunteer application form and we will be in contact as soon as possible.            
        </p>
        <p>
            2. What skills i require to volunteer?<br />
            Each volunteer role differs for the skills needed; however most of our positions have on the job training and are suitable for anyone. Our volunteers undertake a Working with Children Check and a Police Check before beginning. If you have a particular skill set that you are interested in donating , such as gardening or building, please contact our member Coordinator for more information
        </p>
